Have you ever had an epic item in Hate or Fear rot, or be looted for the guildbank/multiquesting because the classes present did not need it? It happened to us with an Eye of Innoruuk and a Hand of the Maestro yesterday.<br>
<br>
I propose an informal network here among guild reps. Each of us can post what epic items from Hate / Fear / Sky our guilds are likely to not need. Let's say all Tindi warriors have the Hand of the Maestro and the blade from Sky. I post a list here saying that warrior epic loot from Sky and Hate is likely to rot on Tindi raids. Then a GM from another guild contacts me, and asks me to take a deserving warrior from their guild as a guest on our raid. Another example is that maybe(?) El'lar Dobluth doesn't need any more earth staves for the mage quest (hehe), and they invite me as a guest to their Hate raids =)<br>
<br>
This is an idea borne out of my personal frustration with  the last item for my own epic, but I really do think that it is also a win-win proposal for everybody. It doesn't require any changes in the calendar rules, and the sooner we all get our epic items from those stupid zones, the sooner we can clear the hell out of there and have fun in Velious and soon, Luclin.<br>
<br>
Shall we do this?<br>
<br>
Datalore <p><P><CENTER>
